## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the PCOS Clinical Dashboard project.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (latest version)
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the complete dependency tree

**2. Analytics Integration**
- Modified `frontend/app/layout.tsx`:
  - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag of the root layout
  - Preserved existing code structure and formatting

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I implemented the App Router configuration for Next.js:
- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body tag in the root layout
- This ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages in the application
- The implementation follows Next.js 16.2.7 best practices for the App Router

### Verification Completed

✅ **Build Verification**: Next.js build completed successfully with no errors
✅ **Linter Check**: No linting errors introduced by the Analytics integration
✅ **Type Safety**: All TypeScript types are correctly imported and used
✅ **Lock Files**: package-lock.json updated correctly with new dependencies

### Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. After deployment, verify analytics are working by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to the analytics endpoint
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the "Analytics" section

### Notes

- The integration uses the `@vercel/analytics/next` subpackage which is optimized for Next.js applications
- No environment variables are required for basic analytics functionality
- Analytics data will be collected automatically once the project is deployed to Vercel and analytics are enabled in the dashboard
- A pre-existing linting error was found in `app/page.tsx` (unrelated to this change) regarding setState in useEffect
